full_content.content: Common reasons your Frigidaire freezer light is not working
The most common reasons your Frigidaire freezer light is not working are a malfunctioning electronic control board, broken LED light assembly or a bad power supply board.
We can help! Our service technicians have repaired over
Frigidaire freezers. We can fix yours no matter where you bought it.
Most common repairs needed to fix a Frigidaire freezer

A malfunctioning electronic control board can keep the light from working in your freezer. The electronic control board receives a signal from the freezer door switch when you open the door and the control board should send current to the freezer light. A failed relay or corrupted internal logic on the circuit board can prevent the electronic control board from sending current to the light. When the freezer light is not working, have a Sears Home Services Technician visit your home and fix the problem. The technician will replace the electronic control board if it’s bad.
How to replace a freezer electronic control board

When the light is not working in your freezer, you may need to replace a broken LED light assembly. The LED light assembly includes a circuit board and the LED lights that illuminate the inside of the freezer. When the circuit board fails, the LED lights won’t turn on. Replacing the LED light assembly can be complicated in some freezers. When the light isn’t working in your freezer, have a Sears Home Services Technician visit your home and fix the problem.
How to replace a freezer LED light assembly

If the power supply board is bad, the freezer will not power up. The freezer won’t cool and the interior and display lights won’t work. If the freezer is equipped with an electronic door lock, the lock will fail to engage and the door may not close completely. This is because the power supply in a freezer connects the incoming power from your home’s electrical supply to the components inside the freezer. It also sends power from the control board to the freezer. A defective power supply board may also fail to protect the freezer from power surges, potentially causing damage to electronic components like the main control board. If your freezer is not powering up, have a Sears Home Services professional inspect it and replace the power supply board if necessary.
Why is the light not working in my freezer?
A burned out light bulb or faulty LED light board could prevent the freezer light from working. A bad freezer light switch, wiring failure or bad light socket could also cause the problem.
Troubleshooting a problem with a freezer light bulb not working
Replace the light bulb when you have a light bulb in the freezer and the light isn’t working.
If replacing the light bulb doesn’t fix the problem, check the freezer door switch.
and remove the freezer door switch as shown in this DIY video:
With the switch lever or plunger extended to simulate the door being open, measure resistance through the door switch spades using a multimeter.
You should measure near 0 ohms of resistance through the switch. If you measure infinite resistance, replace the switch because it’s bad.
If the freezer door switch is okay, a bad light socket or wiring failure is likely preventing the light from working in your freezer.
Troubleshooting a problem with a freezer LED light assembly not working
If you only have one LED light assembly in your freezer and it’s not working, or you have 2 LED light assemblies and both aren’t working, then a failed door switch could be causing the problem.
Test the door switch as described in the section above and replace the door switch if it’s bad.
If one of the LED light assemblies works and one doesn’t, or the door switch is okay, then you may have a bad LED light assembly.
Pull the LED light assembly out and inspect it. Here’s a video that shows how to remove an LED light assembly:
If you see a burned spot or damage on the LED circuit board, replace the LED light assembly.

If your freezer uses 2 identical LED light assemblies, install the identical light assembly in the position of the light assembly that isn’t working. If the identical LED light assembly works, then you know that the non-working LED light assembly is bad – replace it.

If the identical LED light board doesn’t work in the non-working housing or you don’t see damage to a single LED light assembly in your freezer, then a wiring failure or a bad control board could be causing the lighting failure.
service to have a Sears Home Services technician examine and repair the lighting when you’re unable to diagnose and fix the problem yourself.
What to expect when you experience a Frigidaire freezer light not working issue
How is the light not working problem fixed?

Correcting most light not working problems usually involves replacing the electronic control board, LED light assembly or power supply. However, there are many potential causes, so a thorough diagnosis is key to fixing the problem. An accurate diagnosis is essential to understanding how much the repair will be.
Sears Home Services recommendations for a freezer light that is not working

When the freezer light is not working it can be for many reasons. To avoid replacing unneeded parts we recommend having a Sears Home Services professional perform diagnostic tests to identify the root cause of the problem. Our technicians are experienced at diagnosing all types of freezer failures.
What to look out for with a freezer light not working diagnosis

Diagnosing modern appliances without proper knowledge and training can be difficult. Without using proper diagnostic techniques, fixing your freezer problem will only be achieved through changing parts on a hunch. Appliances, especially in the last 10 years, have become extremely advanced, and many models have electronic parts that are difficult to test. DIY repairs on the latest appliance models are becoming increasingly difficult.

full_content.content: Why won’t the interior light in my Frigidaire freezer turn on?
A burned-out bulb, faulty light socket, or defective door switch can keep the light off. Start by checking the bulb for visible damage.
How do I replace the freezer light bulb?
Unplug the unit, remove the cover (often clips or screws), and twist out the old bulb. Install a new, appliance-rated bulb of the same wattage.
Could a broken door switch prevent the light from illuminating?
Yes. If the freezer doesn’t sense the door opening, the light circuit stays off. Use a multimeter to test the switch for continuity.
When should I hire a service tech for a Frigidaire freezer light issue?
If replacing the bulb and testing the door switch doesn’t fix it, internal wiring or the light socket may be at fault. A professional can perform safe electrical repairs.

full_content.content: How Do Chest Freezers Work?: 2025 Explanation
Learn how chest freezers work and how to troubleshoot common problems.

A freezer bag is a specially designed plastic bag used for the cold storage of food in the freezer, offering protection against freezer burn and preserving the food's freshness and flavor over extended periods.

A freezer compressor is a vital component of a freezer's refrigeration system, functioning as a pump to circulate refrigerant through the system, which cools the interior by absorbing and expelling heat.
What is a Freezer Door Gasket?
A freezer door gasket is a flexible seal that outlines the edge of the freezer door, ensuring an airtight closure to maintain cold temperatures inside and prevent warm air from entering.
What is a Manual Defrost Freezer?
A manual defrost freezer is an appliance that needs to be switched off and allowed to thaw periodically to remove accumulated ice, ensuring efficient operation and storage space maximization.
